#!/usr/bin/env python3
# ---
# name: recall
# brief: Session recall — hybrid search, passage extraction, Q&A synthesis, file-touch lookup
# description: |
#   Single cohesive tool for looking back through past sessions. Eight
#   verbs: find (ranked session lookup), dig (passages from a known
#   session), ask (Haiku synthesis with forced citations), files
#   (cross-session file-touch lookup), show (summary + metadata), list
#   (recent sessions), reindex, stats.
#
#   Default `find` is hybrid BM25+semantic with RRF merge. --sparse
#   bypasses the semantic lane for exact-entity queries. Index at
#   <home>/state/history.db auto-builds on first use.
# arguments: "<find|dig|ask|files|show|list|reindex|stats> [args]"
# ---
"""Session recall CLI.

Usage:
  recall find <query> [-n N] [--sparse] [--passages N] [--since DATE] [--until DATE]
                      [--sort {relevance,date}] [--why]
  recall dig <session> <query> [-n N] [--deep]
  recall ask <query> [--session KEY] [--sessions K]
  recall files <pattern> [-n N] [--since DATE] [--until DATE]
  recall show <session>
  recall list [-n N] [--since DATE]
  recall reindex [--force|--embed-only|--summaries-only|--files-only]
  recall stats

Environment:
  OPENAI_API_KEY         Gates the semantic lane. If unset (and the
                          credentials file is missing), find degrades
                          to summary-only with a visible flag. dig/ask
                          require it unless --sparse / --deep bypasses.
  RECALL_DB              Override index path (default <home>/state/history.db).
  KILN_AGENT_HOME         Agent home directory. Required — paths (index, summaries,
                          credentials, registry, conversation archives) are all
                          derived from it.
"""

